   "source": [
    "# 🎬 Media Recommendation System\n",
    "### Movies · TV Shows · Anime\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook walks through how the recommender works end-to-end:\n",
    "1. What is content-based filtering?\n",
    "2. Building a sample dataset\n",
    "3. Feature engineering with TF-IDF\n",
    "4. Computing cosine similarity\n",
    "5. Making recommendations\n",
    "6. Using your own real datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "> **No downloads needed** — this notebook uses a built-in sample dataset of 30 titles.\n",
    "> Once you're ready, swap in the real data (see Section 6)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. How Does It Work?\n",
    "\n",
    "We use **content-based filtering** — we recommend titles that are *similar* to what you've already enjoyed.\n",
    "\n",
    "The process:\n",
    "- Each title gets turned into a **vector** based on its genres + description (using TF-IDF)\n",
    "- We measure how close two vectors are using **cosine similarity** (0 = nothing in common, 1 = identical)\n",
    "- Given your watched list, we find all titles with high similarity scores and rank them\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "Attack on Titan  →  [action: 0.8, dark: 0.7, fantasy: 0.5, ...]\n",
    "Berserk          →  [action: 0.9, dark: 0.9, fantasy: 0.6, ...]\n",
    "                      ↑ cosine similarity ≈ 0.95  →  strong recommendation!\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Setup & Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
