   "source": [
    "## 7. Using Real Datasets\n",
    "\n",
    "To get proper recommendations across thousands of titles, download these free datasets:\n",
    "\n",
    "| Dataset | Source | Description |\n",
    "|---------|--------|-------------|\n",
    "| **TMDB Movies** | [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/tmdb/tmdb-movie-metadata) | ~5,000 movies with genres, overviews, ratings |\n",
    "| **TMDB TV Shows** | [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/asaniczka/full-tmdb-tv-shows-dataset-2023) | ~70,000 shows |\n",
    "| **MyAnimeList** | [Kaggle](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/CooperUnion/anime-recommendations-database) | ~12,000 anime with ratings |\n",
    "\n",
    "Place the CSVs in the `data/` folder and rename them:\n",
    "```\n",
    "data/movies.csv\n",
    "data/shows.csv\n",
    "data/anime.csv\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Then run:\n",
    "```python\n",
    "from recommender import load_data, MediaRecommender\n",
    "\n",
    "df = load_data()\n",
    "rec = MediaRecommender()\n",
    "rec.fit(df)\n",
    "\n",
    "recs = rec.recommend(\n",
    "    watched=['Attack on Titan', 'Breaking Bad', 'Inception'],\n",
    "    ratings={'Attack on Titan': 10, 'Breaking Bad': 9, 'Inception': 9},\n",
    "    n=10,\n",
    ")\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "Or launch the Streamlit app:\n",
    "```bash\n",
    "streamlit run app.py\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 8. Limitations & Improvements\n",
    "\n",
    "**Current approach (content-based filtering):**\n",
    "- ✅ Works with no user data — just your watched list\n",
    "- ✅ Can cross-recommend between movies, shows, and anime\n",
    "- ❌ Doesn't know about user taste beyond the input list\n",
    "- ❌ Can get stuck in genre bubbles\n",
    "\n",
    "**Ideas to improve it:**\n",
    "- Add **collaborative filtering** (find users with similar taste) using the `Surprise` library\n",
    "- Use **embeddings** from a pretrained model (e.g. Sentence-BERT) for richer similarity\n",
    "- Pull live data from the **TMDB API** for posters and up-to-date info\n",
    "- Add a **feedback loop** — user can say \"not interested\" to refine results"
   ]
  }
